cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Hedwig in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "Hedwig: An Outcome-Calibrated Governance Layer for Coding Agents"
abstract: >-
  Hedwig is a local governance layer for coding agents (shipped as a Claude Code
  plugin). For every file edit an agent proposes, it decides whether to
  auto-apply or surface for human review, and calibrates that line per-repository
  from outcomes — learning from reverts and verification failures rather than
  from a configuration written once.
type: software
